                                     6
                             ). Rings B and inner A appear relatively devoid of these small particles compared with the C and outer A rings. Their abundance in outer ring A increases dramatically with ring radius. The very short lifetimes of particles in this size range to various evolutionary processes suggest that sizes are determined by an active accretion-destruction cycle (
