                                 6
                         , 
                                 25
                         &#x2013;
                                 27
                         ), and spermathecal fluids that neutralize aggressive male AG compounds (compare to 
                             Fig. 4
                         ) may also be found in dwarf honeybees where sperm is directly transferred to the spermatheca (
                                 28
                         ), as in 
                             Atta
                          (
                                 22
                         ). However, although phenotypic expressions of these sexual conflicts might be similar, their independent evolutionary origins suggest that the genes and pathways involved are different (
