                         ) of AMPAR-mediated currents to a 500-ms glutamate pulse in outside-out patches of CKAMP44-overexpressing or CKAMP44 KO cells compared to controls (fig. S5A and table S3). The steady-state currents during these 500-ms glutamate pulses were usually too small for quantification in outside-out patches. We thus evoked AMPAR-mediated currents in nucleated patches and found in CKAMP44-overexpressing cells a reduction in both steady-state current and &#x03C4;
